We’ll work through each ratio step‐by‐step.

1. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities can be found from the balance sheet. Here, only current liabilities are provided:  
  Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable = 485000.00 + 143478.02 = 628478.02  
• Total Owner’s Equity (end of period) is given as 13905750.76  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 628478.02 / 13905750.76 ≈ 0.04522  
  Rounded, we can state it as 0.045  

2. Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit is from the income statement = 905750.76  
• Total Revenue is given as 2869560.42  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (905750.76 / 2869560.42) × 100 ≈ 31.58%  

3. Return on Assets (ROA)  
• Total Assets (end of period) from the balance sheet = 14534228.78  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100  
  = (905750.76 / 14534228.78) × 100 ≈ 6.23%  

4. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Accounts Receivable at the beginning of the period is 0 and at the end is 2149792.45, so the average is calculated as:  
  Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 2149792.45) / 2 = 1074896.225  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 2869560.42 / 1074896.225 ≈ 2.67  

Thus, the final solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {'Debt to Equity Ratio': '0.045', 'Net Profit Margin': '31.58%', 'Return on Assets (ROA)': '6.23%', 'Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio': '2.67'}}
